</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaryinnmb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maryinn MB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/27/01 9:13:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.merryband.com/images/maryinn/maryinn_2.jpg width=165 height=177></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sinnaire the Illusionist (Brell's Enchanter BOTB winner)</span><hr size=1> Here's how the enchanter botb was set up...<br>
<br>
6 level 43-47 skeleton npcs are spawned at the edge of the raised platform in the arena.  Enchanters are summoned to the center of that platform (where nothing will aggro) and are given 30 seconds to buff.  Then the idea is to kill the other enchanter using any means necessary (minus certain spells like targeted mez and charms on the other player, as well as the other standard botb rules).<br>
<br>
Problems with this setup... Unfortunately the NPC's would aggro quite easily and even worse &quot;rub&quot; onto other players easily... so you could essentially train the other player.  Most of the fights were VERY quick going only a couple minutes (or less).  Most fights had very little spell casting after the initial buff time.  Now I don't mean to take away from any of the other competitors skills, but I think it's pretty apparent this isn't what most of us expected from an enchanter botb tourney.<br>
<br>
Having said the above, after the first round everyone should have pretty much known what to expect so if you made it that far you were a little better prepared to execute a strategy.  In some fights it looked like melee and hp levels were key, in others there was some charming and crowd control (usually ending in some running from mobs, with the best runner winning), in some it was pure training and running and others had a mix of the above.<br>
<br>
As for me I beat Rahvine (sp?) in the first round... he was level 54 and I am 60.  I buffed with c2, rune5 and shissar and started with melee and some spell casting.  Eventually Rahvine got aggroed by a few npcs and died.  In the next match Ohtar (sp?) who was 57? trained me good and ran around much better than me.  I paniced a bit and died to a mass of npc mobs after running around a bit.<br>
<br>
I was able to watch some of the matches with bind sight and many were similar with a few involving pet casting, immediate charming and some other variations, but most of them ended with people running around with the skeleton npc's chasing them.  The fights weren't very interesting to watch really.<br>
<br>
Sinnaire beat Raege in the finals in the first 2 fights (of a possible 3).  I think the other semi finalists were Bulingit and Ohtar?  I think about 18ish enchanters showed up for the fights.  It was fun and silly and stupid at the same time.  Knowing what I know now I would have taken a different approached and lined up a different set of spells and gear.  I wish there could have been some practice time in the arena with the spawned npcs as well, but it's Verant so... <p>-<a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=998">Maryinn</a> 
