  <br>
  So before heading to the Arena, I bought 60 tiny daggers and 10 normal daggers to use as pet weapons, because a summoned pet would be a lot more dependable than a charmed one, arriving I started asking the only GM there questions like... if we summon a pet can we give it a weapon to duel weild... yes we can, so I thought... dual wielding summoned pet will be my key to winning...  <br>
<br>
Then I sat down to figure out what to use as dummy buffs going through my spell book I came up with 6 fast and low mana costing spells, Fire Elemental Illusion (3.0 cast time), See Invis (2.0 cast time), Streghthen (2.0 cast time), Haze (2.0 cast time), Minor Shielding (2.5 cast time), and Endure Magic (2.5 cast time), following those which totaled = 15seconds with my real buffs c2 (3.5 cast time) and SoS (6.0 cast time).  Then I refined my list... Haze took too long to pop after being memmed so eliminated it, and enc dispell takes off 4 buffs so have 5 dummies would be pointless so I eliminated Minor shielding, would use Fire Elemental Illusion as first buff because it took a bit to pop and I could keep it memmed before hand and also it would give the other enchanter a clear perception that their dispell took off something I wanted, fire ele's damage shield.  So my final list for tourney was...  Fire Elemental Illusion, See Invis, Strengthen, Endure Magic, C2, and then cast pet which would be... 25 seconds total cast time and allow me 5 seconds to change spells, boy was I way off...   <br>
  <br>
  My first match comes up against Maya, start doing my buffs... 10seconds to finish before I start casting... my 4th dummy strengthen, so with 4 seconds of buffing left I start casting SoS because I will have no chance to get off my pet and then start meleeing her, my dummies worked and she stripped everything but my haste, she begins to sieve me and I melee her and sieve her back, she tries to buff herself but I only dispell em, she loses hp while I only lose mana, she tries to back off and ends up aggroing skeletons, which quickly attack me when she runs back past me, we continue to trade the skeletons off on each other, she goes down first and I follow 8 seconds later, as I realize she is already dead and the gms are just looking at me get killed.  Probably my hardest fight of the night, because I had no idea what to expect and was the only one where I died.<br>
<br>
  My second match against Quellren... do the same five buffs that worked so well the first time, I start meleeing him but Quellren doesn't dispell me...  first a skeleton is hitting me then 2 seconds later its not...  Quellren had charmed a skeleton and accidentally trained 2 more, so he runs past me depositing one of the skeletons on me and keeping one on him, his pet attacks the one on me, giving me 2 seconds to ponder wtf just happened and what is he doing?  I realize the one skeleton is his pet and dispell it, Quellren  goes down 1 second later, shortest of my fights.<br>
<br>
  My third match against Bulingit... do the same five buffs and he does his, we both open with 1 dispell, leaving me with my haste still, we continue to melee for a bit and he drops a lot more life than me, he pulls the skeletons in with dispell and it turns into who can run around putting more skeletons on the other.<br>
<br>
  My finals against Raege... First match, do the same five buffs, he does his, he dispells me leaving my haste I continue to melee him while he keep sieving me, periodically he tries to buff himself with rune only to find that I still have mana, he dispells me again getting rid of my haste and I continue to melee him, and he tries to buff himself only to realize I'll always have enough to dispell, when he's at 30% he goes for the skeletons to train and dies shortly after passing me with them.<br>
Second match, he goes directly to a skeleton and to get away from my uber melee, he uses ae stuns and mezzes it.  I not wanting to aggro any skeletons stay in the middle, dispell him once and cast choke on him, alternate those 2, he pulls a 2nd skeleton to use as a pet, when I realize its his pet and just didn't aggro on me, I dispell it, and he tries to ae stun and control em and dies shortly after.<br>
<br>
Not really what people consider the key powers and points of enchantering, but a new test for all us none the less, where we all were supplied with the same info and some adapted and some tried to go with what they knew and wasn't neccesarily the best to do in this competition.  The key to winning I figured was to stay in the center of the ring, not touch any of those skeletons, and just depend on meleeing and dispelling, and allowing the other caster to make the moves and then just counter them, and not to bother with mana sieving because it would be pointless because if you did empty their mana and then charmed a skeleton to use as a pet, they could just Theft of Thought and dispell the charm.  <br>
<br>
And much offense Raege, but your comments after losing were completely uncalled for, both our fights were done differently and I had an average of 80% of my hp left after both fights were done, just because you lost so badly didn't mean I took the cheap way to win, well 2 cheap ways because I won differently both of our times, I never pulled a single skeleton first in any of my matches even though they are what killed every enchanter who lost off.<br>
<br>
Wow, I really need to get to bed now. <p><BR>I just need to be reassured
<BR>Do you just deal it out, <BR>or can you deal with
<BR>What I lay down?
<BR>Sinnaire Du'Pre
<BR>Level 60 Enchanter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubulingit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bulingit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Phantom Menace</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/28/01 3:40:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sinnaire the Illusionist (Brell's Enchanter BOTB winner)</span><hr size=1> My fight info:<br>
<br>
Spell Memorized during fight:<br>
Tash, Chaotic Flux, Color Flux, Entrance, Theft of Thought, Recant Magic, Root, Bedlam.<br>
<br>
-<br>
fight 1: Me vs. Colg<br>
<br>
30sec buffing:<br>
Colg: Made a pet (big mistake). Gave dagger to pet, casted Resist Magic (i think)<br>
ME: Werewolf, c2, bedlam, remem spells<br>
<br>
fight started:<br>
I dispelled Colg first (pet doesn't agro on dispell). Colg tashed/dispelled me. I then snuck tash the skeleton directly behind Colg, since it's undead agro, it attacked Colg first (since he was infront of me), his pet attacked the skeleton. He then inches towards me, doing this made his pet agro one of the skeletons behind me, I trained it on him, while i stand on the side and interrupt his spells until he died.<br>
<br>
--<br>
fight 2: Me vs Belchere<br>
<br>
20sec buffing: (gm didn't shout the 30sec mark, so we started on 20sec)<br>
Belchere: casted resist magic, shissar and rune? (not sure about this)<br>
Me: werewolf, c2, bedlam, remem spells<br>
<br>
fight started:<br>
We both dispelled each other, we both followed with Tash. We then proceeded to melee. During melee combat. I basically just chain casted Chaotic Flux. She casted Torment of Argli (dot) and Dementia on me (nuke) which i resisted, so she lost about (30hp? LOL) that i took out from her through melee while she was casting.  When I thought she's convinced that we're just gonna stick to melee to death, i snuck tash the mob behind her, which then attacked her (again, undead agro is the key) and proceeded to melee her down while she was casting spells on me.  She didn't realize the skeleton was killing her until she was below half health already. After that, hell breaks lose and more mobs got agro, some got trained on her which took out her remaining hp.<br>
<br>
--<br>
<br>
fight 3: Me vs Sinnaire (who ever wins this fight in my opinion would determine the botb champion)<br>
<br>
30sec buffing:<br>
Sinnaire: fire elemental, see invis, shissar, str, resist magic (really sneaky <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
Bulingit: werewolf, c2, bedlam, remem spells<br>
<br>
fight started:<br>
The usual tash and dispell routine. We then proceeded to Melee. I look at her hits and me and my bro were like, WTF!! I said, Oh @#%$, the dagger from ToV. Knowing the fact that she would just butcher me in melee combat, i snuck tash/agro the mob behind her (well wasn't actually sneaky, Sinnaire is a big lady <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , so I had to ran around her to target the skely, which should've given her an idea on what i was about to do). She took out 1 bubble of my hp through melee and i took out about 20hp from her, was pathetic.  After I agroed, hell broke lose, more mobs got agroed and It was just a training contest. I saw Sinnaire running away from me with 3 skely's behind her, I saw her health and noticed it was below mine. I was getting excited cause I thought i was winning. Since nothing was attacking me, I began to cast bedlam. Skelys from behind got agroed and hit/interrupted me, so I ran, me and sinnaire crossed each other and suddenly I'm running behind Sinnaire (doh), I steered away but things were happening WAY too fast, you barely have time to think, actions were just based on experience. We ran some more and next thing I know, I hear my gnome death moan, I looked at my brother and we both tuck our heads down and said, OH @#%$! WE LOST.<br>
<br>
Well, was a good fight. I asked Sinnaire how much hp she had and she said 1950+, I only had 1314hp =P<br>
Regardless of this, Sinnaire thought out her 30 sec buffs well. She casted 5 buffs, the 5th being Resist Magic (which is ingenious).  MR that she probably lacked because of the HP items; our best dispell only gets 4 buffs, leaving the 5th one. Since everything goes by fast, you don't realize things like this. I know that the mobs were on her way longer than they were on me, she just lasted alot longer cause of the 600hp difference. This shows that working hard on your equip pays off in one form or another. Hehe, I couldn't scrounge up enough equip, with the time I had, me and my bro were away the whole weekend. But again, regardless of that, Sinnaire is a great player and deserved to win the title.<br>
<br>
Though I think it would've been more interesting if I was on the other bracket and we fought on finals, best out of 3 match.<br>
<br>
also what happened to kendon? he lost the first round, same with Gerad (but he used mez so he got disqualified). Me, Kendon, Gerad and Sinnaire were the only ones I was really thinking that would make to the semi-finals. No offense to the others.<br>
<br>
anyways, I'll see you guys in Test of Tactics III<br>
/cheers<br>
